The paper deals with the analysis of a Sum-of-Squares semidefinite programming relaxation for the clique problem, which is a well-studied problem in computational complexity theory. This suggests that the paper could belong to the categories of cs.CC (Computational Complexity) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper involves the analysis of random graphs, which could place it in the category of cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also introduces a new framework called "pseudo-calibration," which could potentially fall under the categories of cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) or cs.IT (Information Theory).
